sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I12046
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Activator for BL oscillator with reporter protein, (cooperativity and L-strain -10 region)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part forms the activator part of the Barkai-Leibler oscillator. It has cooperativity for the repressor protein 434 cI (two OR sites). It includes a reporter protein. This part differs from BBa_I12044 in that the -10 site for the promoter region of the Lambda cI has been replaced with the Lac -10 region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ryhsiao
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part has cooperativity for the repressor 434 cI (two 434 OR sites). Also, there is a possibility that this Lambda cI promoter region may be more powerful than that of BBa_I12044 since the -10 region has been replaced with that of LLac. A reporter protein (EYFP) coding region is placed after the lambda cI coding region. This will make it possible to keep track of the lambda cI levels in the cell.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: YFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: enhanced yellow fluorescent protein derived from A. victoria GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Yellow fluorescent protein (EYFP) reporter coding sequence without the Ribosome Binding Site. Modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein and faster fall time for the emission.

Annotated mutation cause a Q81L mutation that appears to not be near the active site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_E0032 yellow fluorescent protein is based on BioBrick part BBa_E0031. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I12040
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Modified lambda P(RM) promoter: -10 region from P(L) and cooperatively repressed by 434 cI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Lamdba P(RM) promoter modified to be activated by lamda repressor (cI) and repressed by 434 repressor (cI). Two operator sites are used for both activation and repression to enhance cooperativity. Additionally, the -10 region from lambda P(L) was used instead of that from P(RM).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ryhsiao
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Bushman, F. D. The bacteriophage 434 right operator roles of O-R1, O-R2, and O-R3. J. Mol. Biol. (1993) 230, 28-40. ; Lutz, R & Bujard, H. "Independent and tight regulation of transcriptional units in Escherichia coli via the lacR/O, the TetR/O and AraC/I1-I2 regulatory elements, Nucleic Acids Research, 1997, Vol.25, No.6 (1203-1210)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The O-R3 site of lambda (17 nt) was replaced by the O-R1 site of 434 (14 nt) to facilitate repression by 434 cI. The new 434 O-R1 is 5'-justified with the lambda O-R3 it replaced, leaving the -10 sequence intact. The 434 O-R2 site replaces the wildtype labmda promoter starting at -5, thereby preserving the 8 nt between 434 O-R1 and O-R2 in the wildtype. The mRNA transcript will contain an additional 9 nt compared to wildtype lambda phage.

This part differs from BBa_I12036 because the -10 region from P(L) was used instead of that from P(RM).
